==English==

===Etymology===
Old French ''tonnelle''

===Noun===
'''tunnel'''
# an [[underground]] or [[underwater]] [[passage]]
# a passage [[through]] or [[under]] some [[obstacle]]
# a [[hole]] in the [[ground]] made by an [[animal]], a [[burrow]]

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[tunneli]]
*French: [[tunnel#French|tunnel]]
*German: [[Tunnel]]
*Greek: [[τούνελ]] ''n'', [[υπόγεια]] [[σήραγγα]] ''f''
*[[Ido]] : [[tunelo]] 
{{mid}}
*Welsh: [[twnnel]]
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
'''tunnel''' ''transitive'' tunnelled, tunnelling
# to [[make]] a tunnel through or under something, to burrow
'''tunnel''' ''intransitive'' tunnelled, tunnelling
# to make a tunnel

===Related terms===
* [[tunneller]]
* [[tunnel vision]]
* [[light at the end of the tunnel]]
* [[wind tunnel]]

